HEADWORD: Genoa cake
<hw>Gen"o*a cake</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A rich
glazed cake, with almonds, pistachios, filberts, or other nuts; also, a
rich currant cake with almonds on the top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>genocidal</ent>⟦br⟧
